Ubuntu
dpkg is the underlying package manager for these systems; it can install, remove, and build packages. What it cannot do is download the dependencies.
The higher-level package management system is the apt (Advanced Package Tool) system of utilities.

RedHat
Red Hat Package Manager (RPM) is the package management system popular on Linux , developed by RedHat. It uses yum (Yellowdog Updater, Modified) for all purposes.

OpenSUSE
The YaST (Yet another Setup Tool) Software Manager. It uses RPM as the underlying package manager.
